<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1104" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1104">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16672.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-02T22:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1915—10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Villa, repulsed last night, preparing for another attack this afternoon.
                            Many bullets crossed line last night and several wounded on this side.
                            Am convinced both sides exerting every effort not fire over boundary
                            line.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>